Blackthorn Resources Says Mumbwa Mining Project in Zambia Remains Viable

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-06-15T13:52:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/blackthorn-resources-says-mumbwa-mining-project-in-zambia-remains-viable.html
Blackthorn Resources Ltd. (BTR)  said the
Mumbwa mining project in  Zambia  remains “viable for us” after
the company’s partner BHP Billiton Plc withdrew.  “It is possible there is something BHP missed in Mumbwa,”
Blackthorn Managing Director Scott Lowe said today in a speech
in Lusaka, Zambia’s capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita at 
